    <briefdescription>
<para>Type-erased wrapper for game logic processors. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1System" kindref="compound">System</ref> uses the Concept/Model pattern to erase the concrete system type. Concrete systems are plain classes that satisfy `HasUpdate&lt;T&gt;` — they do not inherit from <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1System" kindref="compound">System</ref>.</para>
<para>The internal `Concept` base defines the virtual interface, and `Model&lt;T&gt;` adapts the concrete type T, owning it by value. `init()` is conditionally forwarded if `HasInit&lt;T&gt;` is satisfied.</para>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1System" kindref="compound">System</ref> is move-only (non-copyable).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para>HasUpdate </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="concepthelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1HasInit" kindref="compound">HasInit</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="namespacehelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1ada19fc9a37afc91c5d10d92dac890b45" kindref="member">SystemRegistry</ref></para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ulink url="https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/More_C%2B%2B_Idioms/Type_Erasure">https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/More_C%2B%2B_Idioms/Type_Erasure</ulink> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
